# steam-cdn.list — Steam / Valve CDN domains for CIDR resolution
#
# Format: one domain per line, comments with #
# Used by: egress/allowlists/update-cidrs.sh (Phase 2 tooling)
# Purpose: resolve to CIDRs → populate steam_cidrs set (loaded by GameMode hooks)
#
# These CIDRs are only active during GameMode sessions (gaming_temp chain).
# At idle, steam_cidrs is empty — no Steam traffic passes kernel-level.
# Per-app Steam traffic outside gaming sessions goes through OpenSnitch prompts.
#
# Valve ASN 32590 ranges are hardcoded in hisnos-gaming.nft (stable).
# These domain entries are for the CIDR refresh script to cross-validate.
#
# Refresh cadence: quarterly (Valve-owned ranges rarely change)
# Refresh command: sudo egress/allowlists/update-cidrs.sh --target steam
# ASN query:  whois -h whois.radb.net -- '-i origin AS32590' | grep ^route:

# Valve / Steam primary endpoints
store.steampowered.com
api.steampowered.com
steamcommunity.com
cdn.steamstatic.com
steambroadcast.akamaized.net

# Steam game content delivery (Valve-owned servers)
content1.steampowered.com
content2.steampowered.com
content3.steampowered.com
content4.steampowered.com
content5.steampowered.com
content6.steampowered.com
content7.steampowered.com
content8.steampowered.com

# Steam client updates and patches
clientconfig.akamai.steamstatic.com
cdn.akamai.steamstatic.com

# Steam Authentication
login.steampowered.com

# Proton / DXVK compatibility (Valve-hosted Proton updates)
repo.steampowered.com
